<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-07-0372 </DOCNO><TEXT>The report describes the activities and results from 1987 within the Open-SeaProgram of the National Swedish Monitoring Program, PMK. Two regularoceanographic cruises were carried out to the Baltic, two plus one supplementarycruises to the Gulf of Bothnia, three in the Kattegat and five in theSound. Standard oceanographic parameters including nutrients were analyzedand various biological samples were taken, including fish and musselsamples for analysis of harmful substances. From spring to autumn a negativetemperature anomaly of 2-4C was observed in the Kattegat and the Baltic.In the Gotland Deep the hydrogen sulphide has now resided for 10 continuousyears in the deep water.</TEXT></DOC>